CHOLERA, IMPORTED - UK 1996
***************************
Date: Sun, 20 Jul 1997 20:46:57 -0700
From: ProMED-mail <promed@usa.healthnet.org>
Via: Hacsi Horvath <varmint@well.com> ProMED-mail Special Correspondent
Source: Communicable Disease Report Weekly [UK], 7:28. 11 July 1997
Cholera, England and Wales, 1996
The PHLS Laboratory of Enteric Pathogens confirmed and typed isolates from 13
cases of cholera in 1996. Twelve of these cases acquired their infection in
areas of Asia and Africa where cholera is endemic, and the other case became
ill five days after arriving in the Canary Islands (see table).
Ten cases acquired infection in Asia; nine had _Vibrio cholerae_ serogroup O1
el tor seotype ogawa, and one, who had been to Thailand, had _V. cholerae_
serogroup O139.
Two cases who acquired _V. cholerae_ serogroup 01 el tor serotype inaba had
both been to Nigeria.
-----------------------------------------------------------------
Table: _Vibrio cholerae_ serogroup O1 and O139 infections imported into
England and Wales, 1996.
Country acquired ogawa inaba O139 Total
Asia
India 4 --- --- 4
Nepal 1 --- --- 1
Pakistan 3 --- --- 3
Thailand 1 --- 1 2
Africa
Nigeria --- 2 --- 2
Europe
Spain 1 --- --- 1
[Canary Islands]
Total 10 2 1 13
